{{Infobox diamond | caption = Aurora Green Diamond, on display at [[Sotheby’s]] | name = Aurora Green Diamond | carats = 5.03 | color = Fancy Vivid Green | cut = Cut-Cornered Rectangular Modified Brilliant | country = [[Brasil]] | original_owner = [[Scarselli Diamonds]] | owner = Chow Tai Fook | value = [[United States dollar|US$]]16.8&nbsp;million (May 2016) }}
The '''Aurora Green Diamond''' is a {{convert|5.03|carat|g|adj=on}} vivid green diamond with [[Diamond clarity|VS2 clarity]]. In May 2016, the Aurora Green became the largest vivid green diamond to ever sell at auction.<ref>{{Cite web| url=http://www.mining.com/aurora-green-diamond-smashes-records-fetching-16-8-million/ | title='Aurora Green' diamond smashes records after fetching $16.8 million |publisher= mining.com | date=31 May 2016 | accessdate=20 June 2016}}</ref> The record was previous held by a 2.54 carat Fancy Vivid Green VS1 diamond that was sold by [[Sotheby’s]] on November 17, 2009 for $1.22 million per carat according to the Diamond Investment & Intelligence Center.<ref>{{Cite web| url= http://www.investments.diamonds/christies-unveils-the-aurora-green-diamond/ | title= Christie’s Unveils The Aurora Green Diamond |publisher= investments.diamonds | date=8 May 2016 | accessdate=20 June 2016}}</ref> On May 31, 2016, the diamond, which was originally owned by [[Scarselli Diamonds]] <ref>{{Cite web| url= http://www.investments.diamonds/christies-sells-aurora-green-diamond-several-new-world-records/ | title= Christie’s Sells "The Aurora Green" Diamond With Several New World Records |publisher= investments.diamonds | date=4 July 2016 | accessdate=20 October 2016}}</ref> was sold by [[Christie's]] for a record price per carat of $3.3 million to Chinese jewelry company Chow Tai Fook, totaling $16.8 million.<ref name=Forbes>{{cite news |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/anthonydemarco/2016/05/31/aurora-green-diamond-sells-for-record-breaking-16-8-million/#5737d83c2775|publisher=forbes.com |title= 'Aurora Green' Diamond Sells For Record Breaking $16.8 Million |date= 31 May 2010 |accessdate= 20 June 2016}}</ref>
==Current Records== – The largest Fancy Vivid Green Diamond ever to be offered at auction. – The most expensive Green Diamond in the world to be sold at auction. – The highest per carat price ever sold for any Green Diamond in the world at auction. – The most expensive Green Diamond to be sold in Asia.<ref>{{Cite web| url= http://www.investments.diamonds/christies-sells-aurora-green-diamond-several-new-world-records/ | title= Christie’s Sells "The Aurora Green" Diamond With Several New World Records |publisher= investments.diamonds | date=4 July 2016 | accessdate=20 October 2016}}</ref>
