{{BLP sources|date=March 2010}} {{Infobox astronaut | image = Konstantin Kozeyev in the Zvezda Service Module.jpg | image_size = | name = Konstantin Kozeyev | type = [[Russian Federal Space Agency|RKA]] Cosmonaut | status = Retired | nationality = Russian | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1967|12|1}} | birth_place = [[Korolyov (city)|Korolyov]], [[Moscow Oblast]], [[Russian SFSR]], [[Soviet Union]] | occupation = [[Flight engineer]] | selection = [[List of astronauts by selection#1996|1996 RKKE Comsonaut Group]] | time = 9d 19h 59min | mission = [[Soyuz TM-33]]/[[Soyuz TM-32|TM-32]] | insignia = [[File:Soyuz TM-33 patch.png|30px]] [[File:Soyuz TM-32 patch.png|30px]] | awards = {{Hero of Russia}} |}} '''Konstantin Mirovich Kozeyev''' ({{lang-ru|Константин Мирович Козеев}}) is a retired Russian [[cosmonaut]].
==Early life and career== Kozeyev was born in [[Korolyov, Moscow Oblast|Korolyov]], Moscow Oblast, Russian SFSR on December 1, 1967. He is a graduate student from Moscow Aviation Technology Institute and was selected as a [[cosmonaut]] on February 9, 1996. He flew as Flight Engineer on [[Soyuz TM-33]] in 2001.<ref>http://www.spacefacts.de/bios/cosmonauts/english/kozeyev_konstantin.htm Spacefacts bio</ref>
==Personal life== Kozeyev is divorced and has no children.
