'''''Pelolinea''''' is a bacteria genus from the family of [[Anaerolineaceae]] with one known species (''[[Pelolinea submarina]]'').<ref name=Pelolinea/><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Parker|first1=Charles Thomas|last2=Garrity|first2=George M|title=Nomenclature Abstract for Pelolinea.|journal=The NamesforLife Abstracts|doi=10.1601/nm.25254|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Pelolinea|journal=www.uniprot.org|url=https://www.uniprot.org/taxonomy/1649478|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Imachi|first1=H|last2=Sakai|first2=S|last3=Lipp|first3=JS|last4=Miyazaki|first4=M|last5=Saito|first5=Y|last6=Yamanaka|first6=Y|last7=Hinrichs|first7=KU|last8=Inagaki|first8=F|last9=Takai|first9=K|title=Pelolinea submarina gen. nov., sp. nov., an anaerobic, filamentous bacterium of the phylum Chloroflexi isolated from subseafloor sediment.|journal=International Journal of Systematic and Evolutionary Microbiology|date=March 2014|volume=64|issue=Pt 3|pages=812–8|doi=10.1099/ijs.0.057547-0|pmid=24215824}}</ref> ''Pelolinea submarina'' has been isolated from marine sediments from the [[Shimokita Peninsula]].<ref>{{cite journal|title=Details: DSM-23923|journal=www.dsmz.de|url=https://www.dsmz.de/catalogues/details/culture/DSM-23923.html|language=en}}</ref>
