'''Wolf Creek''' is in the [[Yukon Territory]], [[Canada]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eol.ucar.edu/projects/ceop/dm/hydro/sites/wolf/|title=CEOP Wolf Creek Hydrology Reference Site|website=Eol.ucar.edu|accessdate=20 January 2016}}</ref>

==Research station==
A research station at Wolf Creek Research Basin has been providing continuous data since 1992 for [[Hydrology|hydrological]] data. There are three [[Meteorology|meteorological]] stations, a  [[Water well|groundwater monitoring well]] since 2003, as well as specialized instrumentation running continuously for specific projects.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://new.cnnro.org/wolf-creek-research-basin/|title=Canadian Network of Northern Research Operators »  » Wolf Creek Research Basin|work=Canadian Network of Northern Research Operators|accessdate=20 January 2016}}</ref>

It is an important location for the study of snow and climate in the region.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usask.ca/hydrology/papers/Pomeroy_et_al_1999_5.pdf |format=PDF |title=The Snow Mass Balance of Wolf Creek, Yukon: Effects of Snow Sublimation and Redistribution |author1=John Pomeroy |author2=Newell Hedstrom |author3=Jason Parviainen |date=March 1998 |website=Usask.ca |accessdate=20 January 2016}}</ref>

